The company – whose directors were Amina Mulik Ali, ARJ Capital Limited, Sudhir Jayantilal Patel and Billow A. Kerrow, with Jibril as chairman – had expected to rake in millions of dollars by doing business with the diplomatic community in the affluent neighbourhood. ARJ Capital Limited owned Java Coffee House, which Mohamed Jibril co-founded, suggesting links to Paddock Investments Limited as well. 



